It has taken me a week to post.  I am so broken by the loss of my friend, stylist, brother,  photographer @jerrismogul.

You inspired me to reach outside of my comfort zone regarding fashion and beyond!! 

Exposing me to bold colors❤️💙💜, body con dresses, pink suits, and life to the fullest on a Neon prosthetic leg, showing the world that this ain’t nothing but another fashion statement and testimony of your life, to not feel sorry for, but to celebrate🎉.

Thank you for randomly pulling clothes, shoes, sending links of looks and teaching me to be proactive and groundbreaking in my life- through intention and bold statements! 

Thank you for conceptualizing my look for my Grammy nominated album, “Diamond Cut.” Building the diamond curtian 💎, from scratch, dressing me, styling me and directing make-up and hair artists ( many times doing it yourself).

Thank you for dressing me for TV appearances, performances, the Red carpet that have taken place across the world. 

Thank you for being the style manager at the 2019 Grammy Awards, and finding the fabulous yellow dress, as well as styling my family with love @stroyston @margomarlene 

You have led your life with grace, compassion and been unapologetic about your intention.  You have and will continue to inspired us all… 

I am thankful that I have a myriad of memories that are housed all throughout my closet, wardrobe shoes, and jewelry. 

I will always keep your wisdom and teachings close, to remember to “Color block” always, and to reach beyond the “body con” dresses. 

May your spirit continue to guide and inspire us. 

RIP Jerris Madison ❤️😢

Happy Heavenly Mother’s Day to the best mom in the world ! ❤️🌸

It has been a year since she has transitioned and everyday I feel her spirit, guidance and presence daily.  When I am tired, she is my strength. “3 Phases of an Idea” 

1) Preparation 
2) Attack 
3) Follow Through 

Today’s rehearsal with my @berkleecollege rehearsing Duke Ellington’s “Nutcracker Suite”

I teach that “music is a manifestation of life.” The tools that we cultivate in life, we cultivate in music.

The power of an idea is ignited by the preparation, attack and sustained by the follow through.

The power of a musical phrase, a note or series  of notes is the same- Preparation, Attack and Follow through.
